================================================================================
Third-party vendored code
================================================================================

This product bundles a verbatim copy of the "predict_snar" package from the
predict-SNAr code release, which is available under the MIT License.

  predict-SNAr (predict_snar)
  Copyright (c) 2020 Kjell Jorner
  Reference: Jorner, K. et al. "Organic reactivity from mechanism to machine
             learning ..." Chem. Sci. 2021, 12, 1163-1175.
             DOI: 10.1039/D0SC04896H
  License:   MIT

The vendored copy lives at src/predict_snar/. Its MIT license text is preserved
at src/predict_snar/LICENSE, and provenance is recorded in
src/predict_snar/VENDORED.md. The package was vendored verbatim, then minimally
patched for Windows portability (two files: calculators.py, helpers.py); the
exact changes are listed under "Local modifications" in src/predict_snar/VENDORED.md.
snar-qc's own code (src/snar_qc/) builds on top of the package.
